2906, 2017Reminder: Community Alert Siren Test on July 5, 2017The monthly test of the Community Alert Sirens will be conducted on:
Wednesday, July 5, 2017
(at approximately 11:30 a.m.)
THIS IS ONLY A TEST !


The monthly test is described as follows: One-minute “all-clear chimes” will precede and follow a two-minute “siren tone.” Total testing time will not exceed five minutes. It is important to note that the “siren” tone carries a greater distance. It may be heard in areas beyond the reach of the “chime.”
During a real emergency, when you hear the sirens, “Shelter. Shut. Listen.”
Shelter in Place means to:
If at home:

Go indoors;
Close all vents, windows and doors;
Listen for instructions on local cable and radio.

If driving:

Continue driving;
Close windows and vents;
Turn your radio to 1620 AM CitiSOUNDS.

If in a parked car:

DO NOT start the engine;
Close windows and vents;
Turn your radio to 1620 AM CitiSOUNDS.

Listen for the “chimes” sound that will signal the “all clear.


2206, 2017Electrical Reliability ProjectThe Torrance Refining Company LLC entered into an agreement with the South Coast Air Quality Management District to improve Southern California Edison’s (SCE) electrical reliability to the Torrance Refinery (refinery), which will minimize refinery flaring from SCE-related power outages.
Click here to view the project update provided at the Torrance City Council Refinery Workshop on February 28, 2017 under Agenda Item 6B.
About the Torrance Refinery Electrical Reliability Project: 

The refinery’s portion of the project will be built to meet California Electrical Code and Industry Standards.
The permanent solution will address SCE’s electrical supply issues.
SCE will install and connect to their system via new 220 kV underground cables to new 220kV switching station on refinery property.
The SCE 220 kV system connection is on SCE right of way.
Torrance Refining Company will install new 220 kV cables and transformers connecting the new SCE switching station to the existing refinery electrical distribution system. This Phase I is expected to improve SCE’s reliability.
In Phase II, Torrance Refining Company will install new local substations and perform upgrades/modifications to the plant’s electrical distribution system, which will be scheduled to coincide with future unit shutdowns to support continued safe, reliable and environmentally responsible operations.
The project is currently in the permit approval process.


